<p id="mwRg">Differentiating once more with respect to the time, we have:</p>

<dl id="mwRw"><dd id="mwSA"><span class="mwe-math-element" id="mwSQ"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {d^{2}X^{\mu } \over dT^{2}}={d^{2}x^{\nu } \over dT^{2}}{\partial X^{\mu } \over \partial x^{\nu }}+{dx^{\nu } \over dT}{dx^{\alpha } \over dT}{\partial ^{2}X^{\mu } \over \partial x^{\nu }\partial x^{\alpha }}}">
