    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle t\equiv x^{0}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="../I/a1b55e93e892e42c339a92d9b5ab46b709aed597.svg" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:6.322ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="t\equiv x^{0}" loading="lazy"></span>. Then the first derivative of <i id="mwag">x</i><sup id="mwaw">0</sup> with respect to <i id="mwbA">t</i> is one and the second derivative is zero. Replacing <i id="mwbQ"><span id="mwbg">λ</span></i> with zero gives:</p>
