  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="../I/c8d241e7c1b244f18eda3f4a64d1e333e0fb7fb9.svg" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:26.563ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle S=\int {\sqrt {-g_{\mu \nu }{\frac {dx^{\mu }}{d\lambda }}{\frac {dx^{\nu }}{d\lambda }}}}\,d\lambda }" loading="lazy"></span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwjg">We can now go ahead and vary this action with respect to the curve <span class="mwe-math-element" id="mwjw"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle x^{\mu }}">
